'''Ushihiko Shrine''' (うしひこじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in {{jalink|Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734}}{{jalink|Naruto City|Q460812}}{{jalink|Ōasa-chō Ōtani|Q11442037}}.

=== History ===
The year of foundation is unknown. During the {{jalink|Tenshō era|Q1145058}} ({{jalink|1573|Q6678}}–{{jalink|1593|Q6772}}), the shrine buildings, ancient records, and sacred treasures were destroyed by fire due to an incursion by {{jalink|Chōsokabe Motochika|Q1070082}}, but were later rebuilt. During the Edo period it was called Hachiman-gū, and since the Meiji period it has been known as Ushihiko Shrine.

Among extant shrine main halls in Tokushima Prefecture, it is the oldest, and on {{jalink|December 4|Q2310}}, {{jalink|2000|Q1985}} ({{jalink|Heisei|Q234510}} 12), the main hall was designated an Important Cultural Property of Japan.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{jalink|Tamba no Michinushi no Mikoto|Q11368587|Ushihiko no Mikoto}}
* {{jalink|Emperor Ōjin|Q317997}}
* {{jalink|Emperor Nintoku|Q313119}}
* {{jalink|Empress Jingū|Q232803}}

=== Access ===
* About a 10-minute walk from {{jalink|Shikoku Railway Company|Q496531|JR}}{{jalink|Naruto Line|Q861091}}{{jalink|Awa-Ōtani Station|Q4829630}}.

