'''Ushihiko Shrine''' (うしひこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|WD=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Naruto City|Q460812|WD=Q460812|1=Naruto, Tokushima}}{{ill|lt=Ōasa-chō Ōtani|Q11442037|WD=Q11442037|1=Ōasa-chō Ōtani}}.

=== History ===
The year of foundation is unknown. During the {{ill|lt=Tenshō era|Q1145058|WD=Q1145058|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} ({{ill|lt=1573|Q6678|WD=Q6678|1=1573}}–{{ill|lt=1593|Q6772|WD=Q6772|1=1593}}), the shrine buildings, ancient records, and sacred treasures were destroyed by fire due to an incursion by {{ill|lt=Chōsokabe Motochika|Q1070082|WD=Q1070082|1=Chōsokabe Motochika}}, but were later rebuilt. During the Edo period it was called Hachiman-gū, and since the Meiji period it has been known as Ushihiko Shrine.

Among extant shrine main halls in Tokushima Prefecture, it is the oldest, and on {{ill|lt=December 4|Q2310|WD=Q2310|1=December 4}}, {{ill|lt=2000|Q1985|WD=Q1985|1=2000}} ({{ill|lt=Heisei|Q234510|WD=Q234510|1=Heisei era}} 12), the main hall was designated an Important Cultural Property of Japan.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Tamba no Michinushi no Mikoto|Q11368587|WD=Q11368587|lt=Ushihiko no Mikoto|1=Tanba-no-Michinushi-no-Mikoto}}
* {{ill|lt=Emperor Ōjin|Q317997|WD=Q317997|1=Emperor Ōjin}}
* {{ill|lt=Emperor Nintoku|Q313119|WD=Q313119|1=Emperor Nintoku}}
* {{ill|lt=Empress Jingū|Q232803|WD=Q232803|1=Empress Jingū}}

=== Access ===
* About a 10-minute walk from {{ill|lt=Shikoku Railway Company|Q496531|WD=Q496531|lt=JR|1=Shikoku Railway Company}}{{ill|lt=Naruto Line|Q861091|WD=Q861091|1=Naruto Line}}{{ill|lt=Awa-Ōtani Station|Q4829630|WD=Q4829630|1=Awa-Ōtani Station}}.

